---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import StatCard from '../../components/StatCard.astro';
---

<DocsLayout
  title="StatCard"
  description="WCAG AAA compliant statistic cards for displaying KPIs, metrics, and data with optional trends, icons, and responsive design."
>
  <section class="space-y-6">
    <div class="space-y-3">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Overview</h2>
      <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
        StatCard components provide an accessible and visually appealing way to
        display key performance indicators, metrics, and statistical data. Built
        with WCAG AAA compliance, they feature proper contrast ratios, semantic
        HTML, and comprehensive screen reader support.
      </p>
      <p class="text-base text-slate-200">
        The component supports multiple variants, sizes, trend indicators, and
        responsive design patterns. All elements automatically adjust for high
        contrast mode and respect user preferences for reduced motion.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-10 space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Props</h2>
    <dl class="grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2">
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          label
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          The label/title of the statistic. Required.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          value
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          The main value to display (string or number). Required.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          icon?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Optional icon to display (emoji or text).
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          trend?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Trend percentage (positive/negative number).
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          trendLabel?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Additional context for the trend.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          variant?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Visual variant: <code>default</code>, <code>gradient</code>, <code
            >bordered</code
          >, <code>elevated</code>.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          size?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Size variant: <code>sm</code>, <code>md</code>, <code>lg</code>.
          Defaults to <code>md</code>.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          as?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          HTML element to render: <code>div</code>, <code>article</code>, <code
            >section</code
          >.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          role?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          ARIA role for accessibility context.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          ariaLabel?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">ARIA label for screen readers.</dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          ariaLabelledby?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          ARIA labelledby reference for complex labeling.
        </dd>
      </div>
      <div
        class="space-y-1 rounded-lg border border-slate-700/75 bg-slate-900/60 p-4 shadow-sm"
      >
        <dt
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-200"
        >
          debug?
        </dt>
        <dd class="text-sm text-slate-200">
          Show visual debugging information. Defaults to <code>false</code>.
        </dd>
      </div>
    </dl>
    <p class="text-sm text-slate-400 mt-4">
      Use semantic HTML elements for better accessibility.
    </p>
  </section>

